          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer201714222" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3515805134889745832">Even with the long, drawn out beginnings, I still love SEP&apos;s older books to pieces. I hate to admit it, but telling the parent&apos;s story really does add a depth to the H/h&apos;s tale that is incomparable. I think this may be my favorite of the series so far. I&apos;ve been listening to it on audio and the narration is fantastic. Multilayered characters, a story spanning decades, and often villains that you can empathize with. Romance that is super spicy but truly realistic, even though it&apos;s set in a world </span>
  <span id="freeText3515805134889745832" style="display:none">Even with the long, drawn out beginnings, I still love SEP's older books to pieces. I hate to admit it, but telling the parent's story really does add a depth to the H/h's tale that is incomparable. I think this may be my favorite of the series so far. I've been listening to it on audio and the narration is fantastic. Multilayered characters, a story spanning decades, and often villains that you can empathize with. Romance that is super spicy but truly realistic, even though it's set in a world of glitz and glamour. </span>
