    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_43980311" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/43980311" />
    <a title="MB (What she read)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1586349-mb-what-she-read"><img alt="MB (What she read)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1224813098p2/1586349.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/43980311?book_show_action=true">Jan 22, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MB (What she read)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MB (What she read)" href="/user/show/1586349-mb-what-she-read">MB (What she read)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061719882" href="/book/show/6057660-glitter-baby">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1586349-mb-what-she-read?shelf=unfinished">unfinished</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1586349-mb-what-she-read?shelf=romance-contemporary-or-chick-lit">romance-contemporary-or-chick-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer43980311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11467011766587426568">I am not a fan of re-issued romances. This one was disappointing and I could not finish it. Susan Elizabeth Phillips&apos; books have obviously very much improved since this one was written. I think they must have decided to re-issue this one because the main characters show up nominally (and years later) in the new book &quot;What I Did For Love&quot;.<br/><br/>If you are new to Susan Elizabeth Phillips please skip this one and try one of the newer books! If you are a SEP-fan, then this may be worth your while. But be </span>
  <span id="freeText11467011766587426568" style="display:none">I am not a fan of re-issued romances. This one was disappointing and I could not finish it. Susan Elizabeth Phillips' books have obviously very much improved since this one was written. I think they must have decided to re-issue this one because the main characters show up nominally (and years later) in the new book "What I Did For Love".<br /><br />If you are new to Susan Elizabeth Phillips please skip this one and try one of the newer books! If you are a SEP-fan, then this may be worth your while. But be warned that it is very different from her usual (modern) style. It seems to me more like the old Judith Krantz books or maybe Danielle Steel??? than what we have become used to and love.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11467011766587426568" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
