<div id="review_144428966" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/144428966" />
    <a title="Archana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4019276-archana"><img alt="Archana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1402339141p2/4019276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/144428966?book_show_action=true">Jan 29, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Archana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Archana" href="/user/show/4019276-archana">Archana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer144428966" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2459821778808222944">I never thought I&apos;d come around to reading this book, I don&apos;t know why. Despite the author being one of my ultimate favourites, I was pretty apprehensive to read this book. It might have been because a. This book was written way back in 1987, or b. I did not want to venture out of the author&apos;s Chicago Stars series I was totally in love with!<br/><br/>Though categorized under &apos;romance&apos;, this book doesn&apos;t neatly fit the bill. It has more demons than one can count. I cannot imagine a heroine facing so many o</span>
  <span id="freeText2459821778808222944" style="display:none">I never thought I'd come around to reading this book, I don't know why. Despite the author being one of my ultimate favourites, I was pretty apprehensive to read this book. It might have been because a. This book was written way back in 1987, or b. I did not want to venture out of the author's Chicago Stars series I was totally in love with!<br /><br />Though categorized under 'romance', this book doesn't neatly fit the bill. It has more demons than one can count. I cannot imagine a heroine facing so many obstacles, even before she was born!<br />Glitter Baby is one of SEP's best and outshines every 'romance' novel out there!<br /><br />It is the story of Fleur Savagar, an ugly duckling who can't believe she's turned into a swan. Her childhood, at a convent away from her mother, her rise to success (albeit unwillingly) as a model and an upcoming actress, her struggle and downfall with her search for unconditional love and finally her bouncing back to the world where she belonged.. as the Glitter Baby.<br /><br />The first part sets up the events surrounding Fleur’s birth and explains why her mother is such a flawed individual who doesn’t have a full grasp on reality and believes that celebrities are just better than normal people. It is difficult to describe Belinda, but this sentence comes close to it – “Fleur saw her mother for who she was – a weak, frivolous woman who wanted the best from life but did not have either the ability or the strength of character to get it on her own.”<br /><br />The book opens with a scene which gives the reader an idea that Fleur was once at the peak of success, hints at her downfall and describes her attempt at a comeback. You understand that she has been through a lot. But only after you read about 60% of the book and read the opening sentence again does the full magnitude of its importance hit you.<br /><br />Glitter Baby is by no means an easy read. I was literally cringing with suffocation during most of it. But what makes it worthwhile is the essence of the story and sheer respect for a person who has never seen true love all her life. All she had was a bitter reflection of something selfish and manipulative that was imposed upon her and called love.<br /><br />I cannot even come close to describing her stepfather with peace. What comes in mind first at the mere thought of him is the image of an incestuous bastard who is cold, cold. I cannot think of someone who can be so self-centred, creepy vigilant and manipulative!<br /><br />Jake is a tough hero to crack. He has a haunted past and tries to convince himself that he is to be blamed for it, while he is not (obviously!). One cannot even like him initially. But he is endearing, all the same! I loved the chemistry between Jake and ‘Flower’. Theirs is a bittersweet romance which leaves you curious as to what is going to happen to them in the future (Just read Call Me Irresistible :D). <br />To sum it up, I’d say this is one book which is way ahead of its contemporaries and is a must read! Hail SEP! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2459821778808222944" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

