<div id="review_744550700" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/744550700" />
    <a title="Hildy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5033175-hildy"><img alt="Hildy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474498190p2/5033175.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/744550700?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hildy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hildy" href="/user/show/5033175-hildy">Hildy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer744550700" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17281351194336844847">You are not going to believe this but...I enjoyed this audiobook! 95% of the time, audiobooks grate on my nerves. I&apos;ve been trying to make some changes in my life and since I have been spending a lot of my time sedentary while reading, I was determined to make audiobooks work for myself. This one did! Keep in mind, that this did have an annoying interlude of elevator music chiming in every so often in random places, but I would usually just laugh a do a little shimmy and keep listening.<br/><br/>Glitter B</span>
  <span id="freeText17281351194336844847" style="display:none">You are not going to believe this but...I enjoyed this audiobook! 95% of the time, audiobooks grate on my nerves. I've been trying to make some changes in my life and since I have been spending a lot of my time sedentary while reading, I was determined to make audiobooks work for myself. This one did! Keep in mind, that this did have an annoying interlude of elevator music chiming in every so often in random places, but I would usually just laugh a do a little shimmy and keep listening.<br /><br />Glitter Baby was first written in the late 80s so while the fashion and pop culture references are a little dated, it didn't affect my enjoyment. I thought the story held up well over time. It definitely has an old romance feel to it, but it also made me a little nostalgic for those kinds of stories. <br /><br />This seemed to fall under the umbrella of Women's Fiction more than Contemporary Romance simply because the story focuses on the heroine and her life, more than the romance. The hero is not even in the book all that much. It's not really his story. As a little warning, there is a huge backstory at the beginning of the book that I know didn't sit well with some readers. I really liked it, even though it centres around some really messed up people. It helped to set the stage for the whole book. I do feel that this book has a more serious tone than most of the books by SEP that I've read. It was missing some of the fun, the witty banter, and the quirky supporting characters. Having said that, I wasn't sure that I was missing that all that much. I power-read (listened) to this in 24 hours. I was so attached to Fleur and couldn't wait to find out how it was all going to unfold. <br /><br />I think I'm jumping into First Lady next, simply because my library has it available for download and I can't wait to keep reading. And for the life of me, I can't figure out why this is a part of the Wynette, Texas series since there was no mention of Wynette nor Texas in the entire book. <br /><br />Re-read: May 2019</span>
  <a data-text-id="17281351194336844847" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


