<span id="freeTextContainer3377652063894031333">I recently found Susan Elizabeth Phillips and she is a fun read. Her heroines have a reasonable amount of angst and insecurity without being total wimps, her heroes are nicely handsome and alpha without being too overbearing, and the plot has a nice arc and some growth. Read one of the Chicago Star series instead.<br/><br/>Glitter Baby (the book) is a little nasty. The relationship between her mother, and well everybody, reeks of sickness and fouled emotion. Not to go into too many details, but the relati</span>
  <span id="freeText3377652063894031333" style="display:none">I recently found Susan Elizabeth Phillips and she is a fun read. Her heroines have a reasonable amount of angst and insecurity without being total wimps, her heroes are nicely handsome and alpha without being too overbearing, and the plot has a nice arc and some growth. Read one of the Chicago Star series instead.<br /><br />Glitter Baby (the book) is a little nasty. The relationship between her mother, and well everybody, reeks of sickness and fouled emotion. Not to go into too many details, but the relationship between the mother and the "father" is more than kinky and not in a fun way. The hero is not so great either, and there is little build up to explain or show how Fleur and Jake end up loving each other.<br /><br />I vacillated between one or two stars, but I can not recommend this to anyone so one star.</span>
