              <span id="reviewTextContainer2669152709" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3842027616938556220">4.5 stars. Susan Elizabeth Phillips is known for her romance novels, yet I can’t really call this a romance. It’s so much more. This book is epic. It spans 30 years, starting with the background story of an 18 year old girl in Old Hollywood in the 50’s as she tries to become an actress, but instead becomes the pawn in a game between two famous wealthy men. One a famous actor and the other a wealthy French aristocrat. <br/><br/>Many years later, we meet her daughter Fleur who is the Glitter Baby. A model/a</span>
  <span id="freeText3842027616938556220" style="display:none">4.5 stars. Susan Elizabeth Phillips is known for her romance novels, yet I can’t really call this a romance. It’s so much more. This book is epic. It spans 30 years, starting with the background story of an 18 year old girl in Old Hollywood in the 50’s as she tries to become an actress, but instead becomes the pawn in a game between two famous wealthy men. One a famous actor and the other a wealthy French aristocrat. <br /><br />Many years later, we meet her daughter Fleur who is the Glitter Baby. A model/actress. <br /><br />This story is about the vicious games people play and the fallout. It’s about greed, pride, weakness, and reinvention. <br /><br />I’ve come to expect a lot of laugh out loud moments in SEP’s writing, but Glitter Baby was more on the serious side. It’s didn’t make it any less amazing though. <br /><br />There are some pretty sick situations that made me nauseous. I couldn’t stand Fleur’s father or Errol Flynn. They are both sickos. Fleur’s Belinda was also a complete failure as a mother, yet I pitied her. <br /><br />As I’ve said before, SEP writes the best heroines. Fleur Savager is no exception. She’s one of my favorites. <br /><br />This book was so fun to listen to on audio. I loved all the Old Hollywood references, all the high fashion, and of course, the witty banter that SEP is known for. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3842027616938556220" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

