        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1385743107" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer208248386685338501">Five Glittering Stars for Glitter Baby!<br/><br/>I’ll start off by saying that this book nearly got dnf’d. I’m so glad I stuck with it though. <br/>I’m not one to keep up with Hollywood especially the Hollywood of nearly 70 years ago. So when I had to google a bunch of the stars mentioned in Chapter One and gag at all the patriarchy of early 1940 I started worrying that mayyybe this one wasn’t for me. <br/><br/>Boy was I wrong!<br/><br/>Glitter Baby tells the story of the beautiful Fleur Savagar’s rise to success and independence</span>
  <span id="freeText208248386685338501" style="display:none">Five Glittering Stars for Glitter Baby!<br><br>I’ll start off by saying that this book nearly got dnf’d. I’m so glad I stuck with it though. <br>I’m not one to keep up with Hollywood especially the Hollywood of nearly 70 years ago. So when I had to google a bunch of the stars mentioned in Chapter One and gag at all the patriarchy of early 1940 I started worrying that mayyybe this one wasn’t for me. <br><br>Boy was I wrong!<br><br>Glitter Baby tells the story of the beautiful Fleur Savagar’s rise to success and independence. Like me you may be hesitant about powering through the first couple chapters but trust me they’re absolutely necessary and you wouldn’t want the book to begin any other way. <br><br>I can’t summarize the book without giving away it’s beauty but what I can do is tell you is that every single character Susan Elizabeth Phillips has created here for us today deserves a <s> Grammy </s> I'm told that I meant to say Academy Award. <br><br>First up we have the Glitter Baby herself Fleur Savagar <br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1441725987i/16144240._SY540_.jpg" width='“320"' height='“200"' alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Fleur’s mother Belinda Savagar<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1441725791ra/16144220.gif" width='“320"' height='“200"' alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Ok, ok just kidding, here’s Belinda<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1441725791i/16144221._SX540_.png" width='“320"' height='“200"' alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Alexi Savagar<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1441725791ra/16144222.gif" width='“320"' height='“200"' alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><br>and Jake Koranda *dreamy sigh*<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1441725791i/16144223.jpg" width='“320"' height='“200"' alt="description”/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This book was everything I never expected tied up in a hyacinth blue satin bow.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Highly recommend it!" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
